'''Kawaai Shrine''' (かわあいじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in Aisome, {{ill|lt=Ikeda, Nagano|Q1204048|qid=Q1204048|lt=Ikeda|1=Ikeda, Nagano}}, {{ill|lt=Kitaazumi District|Q1155067|qid=Q1155067|1=Kitaazumi District, Nagano}}, {{ill|lt=Nagano Prefecture|Q127877|qid=Q127877|1=Nagano Prefecture}}. It is a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|qid=Q134917286}}, and its {{ill|lt=former rank under the modern system|Q712534|qid=Q712534|lt=former rank|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines}} was {{ill|lt=Sonsha|Q134917284|qid=Q134917284|1=Son-sha}}.

=== Overview ===
The enshrined deity is Sokotsu Watatsumi-no-Mikoto. Located near the confluence of the {{ill|lt=Nōgugawa|Q109361304|qid=Q109361304|1=Nōgugawa}} and {{ill|lt=Takase River (Nagano)|Q11671931|qid=Q11671931|lt=Takase River|1=Takase river}}, it was repeatedly forced to relocate due to river flooding. Shrine tradition says it was built in Hakuhō 2 ({{ill|lt=673|Q31105|qid=Q31105|1=673}}).

In the ''{{ill|lt=Engishiki|Q1342448|qid=Q1342448|1=Engishiki}}'' ''{{ill|lt=Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|qid=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}'', completed in Enchō 5 ({{ill|lt=927|Q30470|qid=Q30470|1=927}}), it is listed as "Kawaai Shrine" in {{ill|lt=Azumi District|Q11450769|qid=Q11450769|1=Azumi district}}, {{ill|lt=Shinano Province|Q289250|qid=Q289250|1=Shinano Province}}, and ranked as a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|qid=Q134917286}}.

It is said to have been moved to the current location in Tenmei 3 ({{ill|lt=1783|Q7745|qid=Q7745|1=1783}}).

=== Precincts ===
Besides the main sanctuary, there are a heiden, worship hall, and gaku-den. A monument to the poet {{ill|lt=Mayumi Uchiyama|Q18336586|qid=Q18336586|1=Uchiyama Mayumi}} also stands in the precincts.
